National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met with Italian Prime Minister Mario Draghi in Rome on March 15 to discuss international cooperation in response to Russia's invasion of Ukraine. Sullivan also met with Luigi Mattiolo, Diplomatic Advisor to the Prime Minister. The discussions focused on imposing costs on Russia for its war on Ukraine, providing humanitarian assistance to those affected by the conflict, and supporting European efforts to establish alternative energy sources. They also talked about Transatlantic approaches to China and enhancing US-Italian relations.